rComments: YouSpark new relationships among your students and a flame of desire forSociology within me.Above sublime teaching methods and delivery of lectures,you taught the most imp. thing,CriticalThinking.ThisWas not new to me yet helped me use it 2most of my ability.Thus,I have been equipped with the best tools to succeed at my undergrad level.Grateful

Professor Laberge extended my boundaries of critical thought in his pedagogy, through texts and lectures that were specifically relevant and essential to a healthy, well-rounded, 3rd year seminar in Religious Studies. He was very helpful. His assignments and evaluations were rigorous if you wanted to snag a higher grade, but also anticipative.

J'aimerais mettre de l'avant la qualité de l'enseignement de Monsieur Laberge. En plus d'être extrêmement sympathique, M Laberge est aussi un passionné, et ça se ressent quand il enseigne. Son enseignement m'a donné envie d'approfondir mes connaissances. De plus, il arrive a amené le groupe a échangé, et cela rend le cours dynamique. Je recommande.

J'ai eu Pr. Laberge deux fois pendant mon cursus universitaire, et c'est l'un des professeurs des plus marquants! Nous avons étudié plusieurs corpus de textes diversifiés, qui ont grandement amélioré ma culture générale, compétence à l'écrit et mon esprit critique,. Il n'hésite pas à aller à la rencontre des étudiants pour assurer notre réussite!

Professeur Laberge, est l'un des professeur qui m'a inspiré durant ma dernière année de bacalauréat de part sa méthode d'enseignement. Il a su captiver notre attention, même si les cours étaient offert en ligne. Ces exposés magistraux, ces lectures dirigées, nos discussions hedomadaires et aussi mes recherches individuelles m'ont assuré un A.

Professor Laberge is amazing! He responds to students' emails soon every time, and he also cares about his students. His lectures were interesting, but there is a lot to learn. I would like to take his course again.

Taking Professor Laberge's course was one of the best decisions in my life. He is a kind, wise, and broad-thinking person. As a professor, he really wants his students to succeed and always brings a lot of useful feedback to his students. Besides, his grading is quite fair; hence, I could get a good mark in his class. Best prof at uOttawa!

Best teacher I have ever had. Dr. Laberge helped me so much, and gave amazing lectures. I learned a lot from him. He is very kind, and caring for his students. He goes above and beyond to help his students. Wish all teachers were like him. Truly a gem, and an passionate intellect! He should teach more classes, would definitely take him again!

His style of teaching and lecturing is what truly sets him apart from other professors in the faculty of social sciences. He promoted a hybrid teaching platform where he lectured live but also recorded the lectures for future viewing. He would greatly concern himself with his students' progress and build rapport with his student body (inclusive)

Amazing prof! Would take any chance to have him as a prof again! Honestly he is a real gem as he is super accessibly outside of class. He is willing to go above and beyond to help students! Really wish he taught more courses! Don't hesitate and take him as a prof!

Prof. Laberge is very passionate about the issues he teaches about. He is extremtly knowledgeable and explains the material in a simple way. He is a joy to be around and his tests are very straight forward. Go to class take notes and youll do fine. Would suggest.

Great professor. Very involved in and outside of class and really knows the material. Lecture heavy but he makes sure all students understand the content before moving on. Very helpful and you can tell he wants his students to do well.

Dr. Laberge was the greatest professor I have had since going to uOttawa! I was a first-year student who passed with flying colours, so what does that tell you? Dr. Laberge truly cares about his students, knows his criteria, and does everything he can to help his students' success!

Super nice guy, just not the best lecturer. His 3h lectures could've easily been 1.5h tops. He is super knowledgeable though and truly cares about his students, he just doesn't always know how to get the info across and rambles on a lot. Overall, a decent prof

Dr. Laberge is a great professor who truly cares about his students! The course content offers critical insight on several state actors and geo-political human rights issues. Extra research outside of the course material may be required to get over an 80% on exams. However, all the material necessary to pass the course is available for students.

I had an amazing experience with this class and this prof. I love this material and Prof. Laberge broke down the material in a way that was easy to understand and always answered questions in class or in a quick and timely manner outside of class. He provided multiple reading that helped with the midterms and exams. Overall really good experience!
Great prof, truly cares about his students. Can't think of any criticism about him.

Was incredibly caring and the content of the syllabus was fantastic. Prof will take time to make the class accessible for everyone and give amazing lectures. The exams are solid if you're prepared for them, just make sure you do the readings!!
Phenomenal professor. One of the best classes Ive taken. Genuinely cares for students, and takes the time to explain and help.

Hands down one of the best professors at uOttawa. He devotes his time to ensure his students understand the material (Readings, lectures,videos). His passion for Human Rights shines through his teaching and it makes students stay engaged and show up for the lectures. I would most definitely take his class again because I learnt a ton in his class.

The absolute kindest professor you will ever meet. It is so clear that he cares about his students and is passionate about teaching. Our class loved him and he never failed to put a smile on our faces!

Professor Laberge is a real gem. He is the best prof I will ever have in uOttawa. He is kind and persistent and understanding. He gives you real knowledge . he makes you learn through all odd's . He is a definition of what a prof should be doing in uOttawa. I will never regret this class in my life. He has opened my eyes in human rights so so much.

Easily one of my favorite professor's, if not my favorite. He really cares about his students! I enjoy his lectures, he's passionate about his career and interests and makes it easy to succeed. No textbook (not for ECH 2300 either), just some decent readings and some short youtube videos. If you put in the work, you will be rewarded!

Yves Laberge became one of my favorite professors. He is so caring about his students and always tries to make time for them. He is not a tough grader; however, I'll suggest reading what he posts on Brightspace to get a good mark. He does not have a heavy Quebecois accent so you won't have any issues understanding his classes.

Readings & videos are very relevant to what was discussed in seminar and what was tested. He prefers essay style questions (gives a bank of questions and expects students to answer at least two in 2-3 pages). He takes the time to meet outside of class via zoom to give feedback (his feedback is very helpful). I learned a lot in this class.

yves Laberge est le prof le plus cute et attentionné que j'ai connue dans toute ma vie. Contrairement aux autres profs il s'intéresent grandement aux élèves et fait tout pour nous. Il est toujours disponible et crée une bonne relation avec les élèves. il est très sociable et très easy going. le meilleur prof. je l'adore.

I am so glad and impressed to have Dr. Laberge's class at my last year in the U of Ottawa. He is one of the best professors I've met during my college life. He is not an easy marker, but every effort you've made will be rewarded. I definitely want to take more courses with Dr. Laberge if one day I decide to go back to school and continue my study.

one of the best teacher CDN 1500 easy marks to get and for the quizzes and finals, he gives you the questions 1 week before and easy grader. If you definitely want to pass a class, take this course with him.
Super sweet teacher. Really kind and very relaxed/laid back. Very flexible and understanding. I suggest him to anyone who's looking to have a great teacher and good grades for not much work.

I had M. Laberge for all the courses he offers at uOttawa - canadian studies, in cinema, and in international development. He's the most flexible prof I've had, he is constructive and his pedagogy actually helps you understand the different themes in class. He wants student to learn without being harsh or tough.
